article.headline: Utah 58, Stanford 57
article.story: SALT LAKE CITY -- Chris Hines scored 19 points, including the game-winning 3-pointer with 27 seconds left, and Utah defeated the Stanford 58-57 on Saturday to halt an eight-game losing streak. The win provided a little salvation for the Utes (6-22, 3-13 Pac 12), who closed out the home portion of their inaugural Pac-12 campaign with a 6-9 record -- their first losing mark at home in 38 years. The game went down to the wire like the first meeting, which Stanford won 68-65 in Palo Alto, Calif. Freshman Chasson Randle had a chance to win it for Stanford but missed a long 3-pointer at the buzzer. Randle led Stanford (19-10, 9-8) with 19 points, including five 3-pointers. Jason Washburn added 17 points for the Utes, who won the game at the free throw line by making 17 of 21 attempts. Dijon Farr added 12 points and six rebounds for Utah.
